I have at times stretched the emu window (many allow you to stretch it to any scale you like). However, I prefer debugging my game with clear pixels, rather than blurred or antialiased ones. I can run the game on hardware anytime I like, so I know what it looks like stretched. Emus don't have perfect palettes, but it's not a big deal either.<br /><br />If one really cares about perfect scaling and such, they should just use real hardware, of it they can't do that, simply resize the window manually, heh <img src="http://forums.nesdev.com/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" alt=";)" title="Wink" /><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=42">Brian_Provinciano</a> — Tue Dec 07, 2004 11:30 pm</p><hr />
